detaileddescription.para:
myIpSettings



Network configuration settings. Pointer contains IP address, Gateway, DNS Server and DHCP information



RETCODE_NULL_POINTER - if the input parameter passes NULL. 

RETCODE_OK - Settings retrieved correctly. 

RETCODE_UNINITIALIZED - if WlanConnect_GetInitStatus failed by returning WLANCONNECT_NOT_INITIALZED. 

RETCODE_FAILURE - if sl_NetCfgGet failed by returning NETWORKCONFIG_FAILURE .

The return value consist of (First 1 MSByte represents Package ID, Next Byte represents Severity and Last 2 LSBytes represents error code) Below shows the error code(last 2 Bytes) meaning
Example usage: Getting the IP settings //LocalvariablethatstorestheIPsettings
WlanNetworkConfig_IpSettings_TmyIpGet;
//Localvariableforstoringthereturnstatus
Retcode_TretStatus;

//retrievetheIPsettings
retStatus=WlanNetworkConfig_GetIpSettings(&myIpGet);

//printamessageifthefunctionreturnedsuccessfully
if(RETCODE_OK==retStatus)
{
printf("TheIPwasretrievedsuccessfully");
}

none







WLANNWCNF_IPSTATUS_IPV4_AQRD - IPv4 was acquired 

WLANNWCNF_IPSTATUS_IPV6_AQRD - IPv6 was acquired (currently not supported) 

WLANNWCNF_IPSTATUS_IP_NOTAQRD - IP was not acquired
Example usage: Block until IP status is acquired and Wlan is connected while((WLANNWCT_STATUS_DISCONNECTED==WlanNetworkConnect_GetStatus())
||(WLANNWCNF_IPSTATUS_IP_NOTAQRD==WlanNetworkConfig_GetIpStatus()))
{
//Stayhereuntilconnectedandipacquired.
//Timeoutlogiccanbeaddedhere.
}

This API must be called only after initialization

ipValue
Hexadecimal value of the IP V4
index
Determines which byte of the IPV4 will be returned.It should be from 0 to 3
On success returns the integer value of IP from given hexadecimal value
any error value refer SL_IPV4_BYTE error codes Example usage: Extract IPV4 byte from the hexadecimal IP value and print it //GettheIPsettings WlanNetworkConfig_GetIpSettings(&myIpGet);
//PrinttheretrievedIPaddress.TheGateway,DNSandMask //canalsobeextractedinthesamemanner printf("-ThestaticIPwasretrieved:%u.%u.%u.%u\n\r", (unsignedint)(WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Byte(myIpGet.ipV4,3)), (unsignedint)(WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Byte(myIpGet.ipV4,2)), (unsignedint)(WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Byte(myIpGet.ipV4,1)), (unsignedint)(WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Byte(myIpGet.ipV4,0)));

add3



Decimal value of the first byte (MSB) of an IPV4 



add2



Decimal value of the second byte of an IPV4 



add1



Decimal value of the third byte of an IPV4 



add0



Decimal value of the last byte (LSB) of an IPV4



On success returns the integer value of IP from given hexadecimal value 

any error value refer SL_IPV4_VAL error codes
Example usage: Transform IPV4 to hexadecimal value //Localvariables
WlanNetworkConfig_IpSettings_TmyIpSet;

//AftercallingthefunctiontheIPV4valuesshallbe:
//0xc0a80278,theequivalentfor192.168.2.120
//0xc0a80201,theequivalentfor192.168.2.1
//0xffffff00,theequivalentfor255.255.255.0
myIpSet.ipv4=WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Value(192,168,2,120);
myIpSet.ipV4DnsServer=WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Value(192,168,2,1);
myIpSet.ipV4Gateway=WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Value(192,168,2,1);
myIpSet.ipV4Mask=WlanNetworkConfig_Ipv4Value(255,255,255,0);

myIpCallback



Callback function for notifying user of IP acquisition using DHCP



RETCODE_UNINITIALIZED - if WlanConnect_GetInitStatus failed by returning WLANCONNECT_NOT_INITIALZED. 

RETCODE_FAILURE - if sl_Start failed by returning other than ROLE_STA. 

RETCODE_OK - sets the IP by using DHCP successfully.

Retcode_T The return value consist of (First 1 MSByte represents Package ID, Next Byte represents Severity and Last 2 LSBytes represents error code) Below shows the error code(last 2 Bytes) meaning
Example usage: Setting DHCP IP with Callback //Callbackfunction
voidmyDhcpIpCallbackFunc(WlanNetworkConfig_IpStatus_TreturnStatus)
{
//usercandosomethinginsidethiscallback
}

//localvariables
NCI_ipCallback_tmyIpCallback;
Retcode_TretStatus;

//SettheIPcallback
myIpCallback=myDhcpIpCallbackFunc;

//ConfigureDHCPIPwithcallback
retStatus=WlanNetworkConfig_SetIpDhcp(myIpCallback);

Example2 usage: Setting DHCP IP without Callback //ConfigureDHCPIPwithoutcallback.
//Notethatthisisthedefaultfunctionincasenoother
//functionisusedinordertosettheIP
retStatus=WlanNetworkConfig_SetIpDhcp(NULL);

simplesect.para:
Retcode_T The return value consist of (First 1 MSByte represents Package ID, Next Byte represents Severity and Last 2 LSBytes represents error code) Below shows the error code(last 2 Bytes) meaning Example usage: Setting static IP //Localvariables
WlanNetworkConfig_IpSettings_TmyIpSet;
Retcode_TretStatus;

//IPsettingsthatwillbeused.
myIpSet.isDHCP=(uint8_t)DHCP_DISABLED;
myIpSet.ipV4=NCI_ipv4Value(192,168,2,120);
myIpSet.ipV4DnsServer=NCI_ipv4Value(192,168,2,1);
myIpSet.ipV4Gateway=NCI_ipv4Value(192,168,2,1);
myIpSet.ipV4Mask=NCI_ipv4Value(255,255,255,0);

//SetthestaticIP
retStatus=WlanNetworkConfig_SetIpStatic(myIpSet);

//printamessageifthefunctionreturnedsuccessfully
if(RETCODE_OK==retStatus)
{
printf("ThestaticIPwassetsuccessfully");
}
